cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.CY 

This paper discusses privacy concerns in data collection, which is a common topic in computer security (cs.CR) and databases (cs.DB). The use of intermediate servers and trust models also involves machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the privacy-utility tradeoff is a topic in cybernetics (cs.CY).
